A culture of pride in “waking up all night” still exists, he added, and noted that modern technology and the ever-increasing pressure on students mean that the problem of sleep deprivation is growing.
Sufficient sleep of good quality should be a student's "secret weapon" to combat stress, exhaustion and anxiety, even with a set of excess weight, since sleep deprivation puts the brain in a mode of hunger that causes constant physical hunger, he said.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian who studies chemical and physical biology, helped Professor Chaser develop the course after enrolling in one of his other courses last year during his first year at Harvard.
